{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6710b2e0-cb56-41b5-9a5d-62fd30d52f1b","content":"**Yes, you will.** MSTest v4 (4.x) dropped support for .NET 6.0 — it requires **net8.0** or later.\n\nYour project targets `net6.0`, so upgrading the `MSTest` package to 4.x will fail to restore or build.\n\n### Options\n\n1. **Upgrade your target framework** to `net8.0` (or `net9.0`), then upgrade MSTest:\n   ```xml\n   <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n   <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"4.3.0\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Stay on MSTest 3.x** if you need to remain on .NET 6.0 (note that .NET 6.0 itself is already out of support as of Nov 2024).\n\nWould you like me to upgrade both the TFM and MSTest for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1887dcfa-fc58-47ce-97a3-5d57bd5c77b5","outputTokens":221},"id":"50ce47ba-5bd8-4a8f-9987-551bbc1dcc93","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:19:59.354Z","parentId":"a28be8e6-4915-42a2-85d7-e0b869e86945"}
